SIMPLE: microcoustic
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Microcoustic
<hw>Mi`cro*cous"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets> + <ets>acoustic</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>microcoustique</ets>, <ets>micracoustique</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Pertaining, or suited, to the audition of small sounds; fitted to
assist hearing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Microcoustic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Microcoustic
<hw>Mi`cro*cous"tic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An instrument for making
faint sounds audible, as to a partially deaf person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Microcrith</ent>⟦br⟧
